  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Monitoring of global trends in science governance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2018-2019, UNESCO will benchmark global trends in science governance by using material from the 2015 edition of the UNESCO Science Report to convey key messages and update notable trends via the report&apos;s dedicated portal. In early 2019, work will begin on preparing the 2020 edition of the report, with the financial support of the Ipsen Foundation. In parallel, a number of activities will be undertaken to help developing countries map their national innovation systems, notably through UNESCO&apos;s Global Observatory of STI Policy Instruments (GO-SPIN).</narrative>
  </description>
